Summary: Procession of Red Glowing Spherical Lights/Fireballs
divs: sighting detailsduring the time of my sighting of what i believe to be a ufo, i saw at my home, standing on my sidewalk and driveway in front of my house. i took my dog outside to go to the bathroom around 9:20\9:25. as she sniffed around my front lawn, i looked up at the sky to see several glowing red lights coasting through the sky above me. unlike anything i had ever seen, i watched for a few seconds while several more of these glowing red spheres passed over my neighboorhood, at one point there was a proccession of maybe 5 or 6 of these objects fly in a group. the first one of tese redlight fireball spheres i saw, i assumed it was a plane, but then realized as there were more and more appearing over a patch of trees, that these were in no way, shape, or form, merely airplanes. i snapped a picture with my cell phone before racing back inside my house to let my dog in, and yelled for one of my parents to come check out what i was watching happen in the sky. i ran back to my driveway, and signaled by dad, who had come to the front door to see what all the comotion was, to come out side and watch. we both watched more than a dozen of these red glowing fireballs fly over our neighboor, then seemingly "disappear". my mom also had joined us by this time in the drive way. by the time this strange event was over, i had snapped 8 pictures of these flying objects with my cell phone. my emotions during the sighting can be described as simply in aw of what i was watching. kind of a surreal feeling to be watching these things fly over my neighboorhood. after words, i started getting very curious about what i just witnessed, and broke out an old telescope and binoculours to look at the sky the rest of the night.
